          "id": "rc-t1",
          "type": "Question",
          "status": "solved",
          "title": "How do I tell schist from gneiss?",
          "authorName": "Sam",
          "authorHandle": "sam",
          "replies": 3,
          "upvotes": 18,
          "askedAgo": "2d ago",
          "body": "I keep confusing them in hand specimen. Both are foliated, both have bands — what should I look for first?",
          "answer": {
            "authorName": "Priya R.",
            "authorHandle": "priya-r",
            "isMentor": true,
            "body": "Look at the banding — gneiss has distinct light/dark bands (compositional), schist is more flaky and uniform. Here's a sample from the dataset: rock_samples.csv → rows 14-22.",
            "upvotes": 24,
            "answeredAgo": "1d ago"
          }
        },
