          "id": "rc-t4",
          "type": "Question",
          "status": "open",
          "title": "Best way to read a ternary diagram?",
          "authorName": "Zara N.",
          "authorHandle": "zara-n",
          "replies": 2,
          "upvotes": 11,
          "askedAgo": "5h ago",
          "body": "Always get the directions mixed up. Any mnemonic?",
          "answer": {
            "authorName": "Bilal A.",
            "authorHandle": "bilal-a",
            "isMentor": true,
            "body": "Read along the side opposite the vertex of the component you want. So if you're plotting Quartz %, follow the line parallel to the opposite side — it bends toward the Quartz vertex.",
            "upvotes": 9,
            "answeredAgo": "3h ago"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "rc-t5",
